      <scopecontent id="aspace_4f7b5c3176958dd781db64f55d0fb9ff">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>Photographs and photograph albums compiled by Ruth Wilhelmina Kohlstedt Benson and Eloise Jeanette Benson Nicholl documenting the Benson family in California, circa 1908-1947. Images are primarily formal and informal group and individual portraits of mostly identified men, women, and children chiefly in Big Bear City, La Crescenta, Los Angeles, and San Diego, California, but also in Indiana and other identified locations. Multiple photographs show the Benson family in Guadalajara, Mexico.</p>
         <p>Photographs also document James Bernard Benson's military service in Savenay, France, during World War I and William John Nicholl's military service in the American South during World War II. Malcolm Daniel Benson and Phyllis Pearl Benson appear in the albums as well.</p>
         <p>Also present are a scrapbook and papers relating to the Benson's cottage at Big Bear Lake, 1929-2003.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
